TinyFugue on Unix-like systems
==============================

TinyFugue requires an ANSI C compiler, BSD-style select(), CMake 3.20 or
newer, and PCRE 1. ICU, TLS, termcap/curses, and zlib are optional and are
enabled automatically when found.

From the repository root:

    make
    make test
    make install PREFIX=/desired/prefix

The Makefile delegates to CMake. For direct control:

    cmake -S . -B build -DBUILD_TESTING=ON
    cmake --build build
    ctest --test-dir build --output-on-failure
    cmake --install build --prefix /desired/prefix

Optional dependencies use `AUTO`, `ON`, or `OFF` modes:

    cmake -S . -B build \
        -DTF_WIDECHAR=ON \
        -DTF_TLS=AUTO \
        -DTF_TERMCAP=AUTO \
        -DTF_ZLIB=AUTO

Use `TF_TERMCAP_LIBRARY` to prefer a specific termcap-compatible library,
`TF_MAILDIR` to set a mail spool directory, and `TF_EXTRA_INCLUDE_DIRS` or
`TF_EXTRA_LIBRARY_DIRS` for dependencies in nonstandard locations.

Supported CI targets are Linux, macOS, FreeBSD, and Cygwin. Scheduled jobs
also exercise NetBSD, OpenBSD, and Solaris. Older Unix variants remain
best-effort portability targets.

With Docker and `act` installed, run the complete Linux matrix locally:

    make ci-local

The non-Linux jobs use hosted operating systems or VM actions and are not
fully reproduced by this local command.
